WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.600
DPO starts from a chosen and rejected answer for the same prompt. The local goal is to raise the winner-loser gap.

00:05.600 --> 00:11.500
Subtract the frozen reference policy’s preference gap from the trainable policy’s gap. Beta controls update strength.

00:11.500 --> 00:17.700
A log-sigmoid loss rewards positive relative margin and smoothly penalizes negative margin.

00:17.700 --> 00:22.400
The paper turns reference-relative preference optimization into a supervised logistic objective. Data, beta, and the reference still matter.

00:22.400 --> 00:29.800
The authors report competitive results with a simpler loop. Check: if both gaps rise equally, their difference and the DPO margin stay fixed.
